              <div type="commentary">
                 <p>Each line of text runs continuously from A to b to C to d.
</p><p>The word siṁsiṁ* is frequently spelled with the special anusvāra at the end, called ulu ricem in modern Balinese. This seems to be the earliest dated occurrence of the sign, the next one Rumwiga I, and it is also found in Sugih Manek from Malang.</p>
